title: NODE JS
text: Node.js is a cross-platform, open-source server environment that can run on Windows, Linux, Unix, macOS, and more.

title: EXPRESS JS
text: Express.js, or simply Express, is a back end web application framework for building RESTful APIs with Node.js, released as free and open-source software under the MIT License

title: SQL
text: Structured Query Language, is a domain-specific language used in programming and designed for managing data held in a relational database management system, or for stream processing in a relational data stream management system
